-- Greece Won’t Raise Power Prices Again in 2012, Naftemporiki Says
-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 2012-01-11T08:15:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/greece-won-t-raise-power-prices-again-in-2012-naftemporiki-says.html
Greece  won’t impose any further
electricity tariff increases in 2012, Naftemporiki  newspaper
reported , citing  George Papaconstantinou , the energy, climate
change and environment minister .  The ministry announced average tariff increases of 9.2
percent from Jan. 1 for  Public Power Corp SA (PPC) , the biggest
electricity supplier, to help the company service its debt and
remain profitable.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  